zboard.com/bluclin71335.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sbik>Sbik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gnomish Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/01 3:50:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=796.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragon loot - opinions please.</span><hr size=1> Here are my opinions on Naggy / Vox loot and how it should be handled.<br>
<br>
First off, haste items.  In my opinion, warriors, paladins, and shadowknights should get two rolls on CoF and RBB since their epics don't give haste and these are just about the best haste items they will ever get (PoA haste belts are better, but very hard to get for most).  Yes Rangers, rogues and monks should get a shot at 'em too, but their epics are relatively easy to complete and have sick haste on 'em (doh.  monk epic is haste spell.  I'm a goober).  I say treat 'em like the dragon bags you give to monks.  Everyone would use 'em, but monks just get more outta the bags so they get preferrential (sp?) treatment usually.  Also, I don't think bards should be allowed to roll on the haste items really.   Yes they get dual wield; dual wield + double attack = nice.   Dual wield - double attack = crap.  Offhand damage is about 30% of what primary hand damage is, so you will do more damage only double attacking with one weapon then only dual wielding two weapons of the same ratio.  Yes paladins and shadowknights don't get dual wield, but they DO get nice 2 handed weapons and very nice one handers.  Plus, 2 handed weapons have a much higher damage bonus to 'em.  Basically, double attack &gt; dual wield.<br>
<br>
I say the Staff of Forbidden Rights should go to people who are known to do lots of corpse recovery, especially those who have feign death or are rogues.  That staff is very handy if say, a raid gets wiped out by Inny and a gnome rogue needs to sneak to Inny's room on 2nd floor and rez a cleric so the raid can continue, hypothetically speaking of course.  =)<br>
<br>
Orb of Tishan.  I say this should be bard only or randomed between EVERYONE there.  I don't believe any caster when they say they *need* this item, mostly because I see 'em selling them so often in E. Commons.  The only person who will really use this will be a bard since they will actually melee with it.  Maybe.  Otherwise, just let everyone have a chance to sell it in E. Commons since that's what's gonna happen anyhow.<br>
<br>
Bladestopper.  I think all who can use and will use should get a shot at it.  Yes, that includes rogues.  I keep a shield on me at all times.  Why?  I pull alot and also do a lot of corpse recovery.  Extra AC is nice when pulling or when you are draggin' a corpse through Hate and a liche spots you.  Gives you extra time to get to a nice spot to die.  Also, it's the best shield a rogue will ever get, period.  Pallies, Sk's and the rest can use Sarnak Battle Shields which are comparable or better.  Rogues can't.  Heck, just about the best shield a rogue will ever see is that crazy velium round shield and it's only AC 15.  Hehe, anyhow, rogues actually don't take much of a damage penalty from using a shield at all times.  Primary hand and backstab make up around 88% of my damage output, so I'd only lose 12% damage output but would gain a TON of AC and hps.<br>
<br>
As for the scales, I say the white scales go to bards who need for epics without a doubt.  Red dragon scales are a different issue since you there are more sources of red scale.  Thanks to always drop red dragon scales, Scalekeeper in the Hole!<br>
<br>
Crystalline spear should definitely go to a rogue there who needs it and won't go sell it 3 hours later.  If none are there, then again, I say EVERYONE should get to roll on it since I highly doubt any of the other people there who can use it, will.  Crystalline spear with backstab = nice.  Crystalline spear without backstab = heavy, slow, pointed stick that will probably just get sold to a rogue twink.  Before Kunark, the Crystalline spear was the end all, be all rogue weapon really.  Now days, most rogue twinks have better weapons at lvl 20  /rude Trak Tooth.<br>
<br>
ok.  enough of my mad rantings.<br>
